## C. Security Architecture

### 1. Digital Signature Security

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  E-SIGNATURE FLOW                                            │
│                                                              │
│  1. User draws signature on HTML Canvas                      │
│  2. Canvas → toDataURL('image/png') → Base64 string          │
│  3. Auto-append metadata:                                    │
│     - Clear name (from user profile)                         │
│     - Timestamp (server-side, not client)                    │
│     - IP Address (from request context)                      │
│  4. Store as text field in eform_signatures table            │
│  5. For PDF generation: embed as PNG image                   │
│                                                              │
│  SECURITY NOTES:                                             │
│  - Timestamp ALWAYS from server (Date.now() on backend)      │
│  - Signature immutable once saved (no update endpoint)       │
│  - Audit log tracks all signing events                       │
│  - Non-repudiation via user session JWT correlation          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 2. Credential Encryption Strategy (AES-256-GCM)

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  CREDENTIAL ENCRYPTION / DECRYPTION FLOW                     │
│                                                              │
│  ENCRYPT (ICT Admin writes credentials):                     │
│  ┌──────────┐                                                │
│  │ Plaintext │──▶ AES-256-GCM Encrypt                        │
│  │ username  │    Key: ENV.EFORM_ENCRYPTION_KEY (32 bytes)   │
│  │ password  │    IV:  crypto.randomBytes(12) per-record      │
│  └──────────┘    ──▶ Stored in DB: ciphertext + iv + authTag │
│                                                              │
│  DECRYPT (Requester reads credentials):                      │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐                    │
│  │ 1. GET /eform-request/:id/credentials│                    │
│  │ 2. Guard: req.user.id === requesterId│ ← CRITICAL         │
│  │ 3. Decrypt server-side               │                    │
│  │ 4. Return plaintext via HTTPS         │                    │
│  │ 5. Frontend shows in masked field     │                    │
│  │    (copy-to-clipboard, auto-hide)    │                    │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────┘                    │
│                                                              │
│  WHO CAN READ:                                               │
│  ✅ Original requester (verified via JWT userId)             │
│  ❌ Manager — cannot read                                    │
│  ❌ Other ICT agents — cannot read post-provision            │
│  ❌ Any SQL dump — encrypted in database                     │
│                                                              │
│  ENV REQUIRED:                                               │
│  EFORM_ENCRYPTION_KEY=<64-char hex string>                   │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 3. Authorization Matrix

| Action | USER | MANAGER | AGENT | ADMIN |
|--------|------|---------|-------|-------|
| Create request | ✅ Own | ✅ Own | ✅ Own | ✅ Any |
| Sign as requester | ✅ Own | ✅ Own | ✅ Own | ✅ Any |
| View own requests | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Approve as manager | ❌ | ✅ Assigned | ❌ | ✅ |
| Confirm as ICT | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Provision credentials | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Read credentials | ✅ Own | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| Reject request | ❌ | ✅ Stage 2 | ✅ Stage 3 | ✅ |
| View all requests | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |

